Pre-heat your #oven{} to 200 degrees. Cut the core out of the @red pepper{1} and
slice it into finger-sized pieces about 2cm wide. Cut the @courgette{1} in half
lengthways and then cut each half into 2cm half moon slices.

Pop your veggies on a #baking tray{} with @oil{1%tbsp}, @salt{1/4%tsp} and a
good grind of @pepper{} and cook in the oven on the second shelf for
~{30%minutes} until crispy on the outside.

Unroll the @puff pastry sheet{1} onto a baking tray. Leaving a 2cm border
around the edges, crumble your @ricotta cheese{1} onto the pastry so it is
evenly dotted around.

> Tip: If you're struggling with crumbling your ricotta (or if you're not a fan
> of the mess!), use a teaspoon to put little 'dollops' around the pastry
> instead.

Sprinkle the @diced chorizo{1} over the top and finally dot bits of your
@Tracklements fig relish{1} over the top.

If you have any @milk{}, lightly brush the border of the tart, then pop it on
the top shelf of the oven to cook for ~{20%minutes}. The tart is cooked when
the outsides are puffed up and golden.

While your dinner is in the oven, give your kitchen a quick tidy (you may even
get all the washing up done before you eat!) and get your taste buds mentally
prepared.

When the veggies are roasted and the tart golden and delicious, get them out
of the oven. Tear some @basil{1/2} leaves over your tart and serve it with your
crispy veggies… enjoy!